description.narrative: Despite continued underfunding, UNICEF provided a multi-sectoral and integrated emergency response in a context of shocks and crises related to population displacements, food insecurity and malnutrition, disease outbreaks (measles, cholera, polio) and floods. UNICEF continued its efforts to strengthen the national system for emergency preparedness and response (EPR) and played an active role in coordinating the response through cluster facilitation and participation in interagency planning for the development of HNO and HRP. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:08/02/2020
